FBIS3-30560 "dreeu025_i_94018" FBIS-EEU-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Internal Affairs Minister Bans Public Gatherings LD0502191994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 5 Feb 94 LD0502191994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] We have just received a statement from the Internal Affairs Ministry Information Service. We carry the statement in full: In accordance with the decision of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina of 5 February this year, Internal Affairs Minister Bakir Alispahic has issued an order banning all public gatherings from 0500 to 2200 on the territory of Bosnia-Herzegovina. [Words indistinct] and other open air public places where humanitarian and other aid is distributed. Exempt from this order are members of the Internal Affairs Ministry directly in charge of duties within the sphere of internal affairs [police], members of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army on military duty, firemen, and medical teams. Appropriate measures will be taken against all those who do not comply with this order.
